results.name: Featured
results.description: Yeah, Featured... it appears to be something default to DeviantArt and it features a random number of submissions that can be manually altered. So far, I have tried to update this folder a few times but in the end I have just given up. This album is a random selection of all my posts and I will just keep them in here as "featured".

results.name: Hands
results.description: Apparently, I have a fetish for hands. I was not aware of it but according to one of the definitions of fetish: an interest in an activity or object that makes someone spend an unreasonable amount of time doing it or thinking about it, could qualify me. I seriously doubt that the time I spend on photographing hands is unreasonable but who am I to determine what is or is not reasonable.  I admire hands and have spent a lot of time photographing them as I love the messages that they can convey, the things that they can do and hands tell a lot about people in general. Hands are used to make art, to play instruments, to draw, to write, to salute, to sexually satisfy themselves and others. Hands are a part of a person that defines their personality and it is often overlooked. When my account on one of the Meta platforms was deleted with  over 10k fans for having posted an image of a hand that was  deemed against the rules and regulations of the platform, my quest for a series on hands started. I searched for art, sculptures, graffiti, and the use of hands by my models.

results.name: Portraits
results.description: A smile costs nothing but gives much. It enriches those who receive without making poorer those who give. It takes but a moment, but the memory of it can last forever. Yet a smile cannot be bought, begged, borrowed, or stolen, for it is something that is of no value to anyone until it is given away. Some people are too tired to give you a smile. Give them one of yours, as no one needs a smile so much as those who have no more to give.

results.name: NIP Nude In Public
results.description: We all come into, and leave  this world completely  naked. During our lives, we tend to cover up and hide in an artificial skin that often defines us. This  series is about capturing the pure beauty of the human form in the urban world.  I am sorry for the fact that these images s appear invisible but as they feature the nude female form, one has to log in to be able to see them. If you do not see them, perhaps it is time to create a free account.
